## Cycle 4 scope (strict)
IN SCOPE:
- `worldcup_playoff/models/hybrid.py`: primary predictor — a Groll-Ley-Zeileis style Random-Forest / Gradient-Boosting HYBRID (arXiv 1806.03208) that consumes Poisson attack/defence abilities + Elo (home_elo/away_elo/elo_diff) + Cycle-3 covariates (form, rest days, goal diff, ranking, confederation) to predict PER-MATCH GOALS (home_goals & away_goals), from which a W/D/L distribution and goal margin are derived. Goal-based so it preserves goal margin for group goal-difference tiebreaks and models draws.
- `worldcup_playoff/models/ordered_logit.py`: secondary/fallback — an Elo-diff ordered logit using statsmodels OrderedModel (statsmodels.miscmodels.ordinal_model), 3 ordered outcomes (away win < draw < home win), returns W/D/L probabilities.
- Keep legacy SVM/RF/NB in `models/classifiers.py` as the backtest baseline ONLY (do NOT rebuild them).
- Time-aware training: chronological split, shuffle=False, deterministic given a seed.
- New tests for both modules; existing suite (711 collected tests) stays green.

OUT OF SCOPE (Cycle 5 — do NOT include): RPS/log-loss/Brier scoring + WC2014/18/22 backtest harness, odds scraping (data/odds.py), tournament/Monte-Carlo simulation + title odds, NEW CLI commands (train-hybrid/backtest/forecast). This cycle may only STUB config needed to fit.

## Inputs the models consume (already built)
