2026-06-24 01:39:48,439 DEBUG msg #250: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01E85BnERQcoJHrAVhFYZSNp): 1	"""
2	Source-blind example tests for issue #10 criterion 1:
3	
4	    Given an in-memory martj42 frame containing unplayed FIFA World Cup rows,
5	    wc2026_features(...) returns those rows with the full feature schema and
6	    home_goals/away_goals as <NA>.
7	
8	Tests are derived solely from the acceptance criteria and requirements.md.
9	No implementation source was read; these tests describe the contract the
10	implementation must satisfy (Red phase of TDD).
11	
12	Choices recorded where the spec is silent:
13	  - wc2026_features resides in worldcup_playoff.features.wc2026.
14	  - Its signature mirrors FeatureBuilder.build(): (results_df, elo_df,
15	    abilities [, ranking_df, cfg]) — the same pre-computed inputs that the
16	    full-history builder already accepts (issue #9).
17	  - Input DataFrame uses the uppercase martj42 internal schema
18	    (DATE, HOME_TEAM, AWAY_TEAM, HOME_GOALS, AWAY_GOALS, TOURNAMENT, NEUTRAL)
19	    consistent with test_feature_builder.py.
20	  - Feature output uses lowercase column names (home_goals, away_goals,
21	    home_team, away_team, tournament) as observed in FeatureBuilder.build()
22	    output in test_feature_builder.py.
23	  - Unplayed rows are identified by HOME_GOALS.isna() in the results frame.
24	
25	Criteria skipped (NOT VERIFIABLE per oracle):
26	  - WC2026 fixture features equal what the full-history builder produces for
27	    the same rows (consistency / single covariate code path).
28	  - No-key path produces a usable WC2026 frame without any API key.
29	  - Deterministic given the seed.
30	  - All tests pass / SOLID quality gates.
31	"""
32	
33	from __future__ import annotations
34	
35	import pandas as pd
36	from hypothesis import given, settings, strategies as st
37	
38	from worldcup_playoff.config import FeatureBuildConfig
39	from worldcup_playoff.features.build import TeamAbilities
40	
41	# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
42	# Shared helpers — derived from data contracts in requirements.md
43	# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
44	
45	_CFG = FeatureBuildConfig(random_seed=42)
46	
47	
48	def _matches(rows: list[dict]) -> pd.DataFrame:
49	    """Build a results DataFrame in the martj42 uppercase internal schema."""
50	    return pd.DataFrame(
51	        {
52	            "DATE": pd.to_datetime([r.get("date", "2026-06-20") for r in rows]),
53	            "HOME_TEAM": [r["home"] for r in rows],
54	            "AWAY_TEAM": [r["away"] for r in rows],
55	            "HOME_GOALS": pd.array([r.get("home_goals", pd.NA) for r in rows], dtype="Int64"),
56	            "AWAY_GOALS": pd.array([r.get("away_goals", pd.NA) for r in rows], dtype="Int64"),
57	            "TOURNAMENT": [r.get("tournament", "Friendly") for r in rows],
58	            "NEUTRAL": [r.get("neutral", True) for r in rows],
59	        }
60	    )
61	
62	
63	def _elo(rows: list[dict]) -> pd.DataFrame:
64	    """Pre-computed Elo DataFrame aligned row-for-row with the matches."""
65	    return pd.DataFrame(
66	        {
67	            "home_elo": [float(r.get("home_elo", 1500)) for r in rows],
68	            "away_elo": [float(r.get("away_elo", 1500)) for r in rows],
69	        }
70	    )
71	
72	
73	def _abilities(*team_names: str) -> TeamAbilities:
74	    """Build a uniform TeamAbilities for the named teams."""
75	    return TeamAbilities(
76	        attack={t: 1.3 for t in team_names},
77	        defence={t: 0.9 for t in team_names},
78	        home_adv=0.0,
