2026-06-24 01:44:25,447 DEBUG msg #363: assistant (tool_use) tool_use(Bash): {'command': 'cd "/Volumes/External SSD/worldcup-2026-prediction" && gh issue create \\\n  --title "feat: Elo-diff ordered logit secondary model (statsmodels)" \\\n  --milestone "Cycle 4 — Groll Hybrid & Baselines" \\\n  --label "phase:implement,priority:high,area:models,agent:python-pro" \\\n  --assignee "@me" \\\n  --body "$(cat <<\'EOF\'\n## Goal\nImplement the strong secondary/fallback predictor: an Elo-diff ordered logit using statsmodels `OrderedModel` over the three ordered outcomes (away win < draw < home win), returning calibrated W/D/L probabilities. It is the lightweight safety net when the goal hybrid cannot fit (e.g. too few played rows); by design it predicts only W/D/L, not goals.\n\n## Context\nConsumes the shared `worldcup_playoff/models/dataset.py` (dependency): `MatchDataset` provides the chronological no-shuffle split and the `y_outcome` target encoded away=0 < draw=1 < home=2 by `outcome_label`/`add_targets` — reuse that exact encoding so both Cycle-4 models share one outcome definition. The predictor feature is `elo_diff` (venue-agnostic `home_elo − away_elo`, already a column in the feature frame from `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`).\n\n`statsmodels` is NOT yet a project dependency (`pyproject.toml` `[project] dependencies`). `OrderedModel` lives at `statsmodels.miscmodels.ordinal_model.OrderedModel`. Ordered-logit MLE (BFGS over a convex objective) is deterministic given the same data — no RNG.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Fits an ordered logit on the `y_outcome` (away<draw<home) target using `elo_diff` (config-driven feature list).\n- [ ] `predict` returns `OutcomeProbabilities` rows with `prob_home + prob_draw + prob_away == 1` (within tol), each in [0,1].\n- [ ] Monotonicity sanity: larger positive `elo_diff` yields larger `prob_home`.\n- [ ] Time-aware: `fit` trains on `MatchDataset.train` only — no internal split/shuffle.\n- [ ] Deterministic: two fits on identical data give identical coefficients/predictions.\n- [ ] `statsmodels` added as a runtime dependency; the no-key path works.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #12: feat: time-aware match dataset utility + Hybrid/OrderedLogit config models\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Modify:** `pyproject.toml` — add `"statsmodels>=0.14"` to `[project] dependencies` (after `scipy`); reinstall with `pip install -e ".[dev]"`.\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/models/ordered_logit.py` — `OutcomeProbabilities` frozen dataclass; thin `OrderedLogitModel` class (`__init__(config: OrderedLogitConfig)`, `fit(dataset) -> Self`, `predict(df) -> list[OutcomeProbabilities]`); `fit_ordered_logit(features, config)` factory. Fit `OrderedModel(endog=y_outcome, exog=X[config.features], distr="logit").fit(method="bfgs", maxiter=config.maxiter, disp=False)`; `.predict` returns (n,3) probs whose columns map to the away<draw<home order. **Lazy-import** `OrderedModel` inside `fit` so importing the module doesn\'t hard-require statsmodels at collection time. Docstring must state this is the W/D/L-only secondary/fallback (no goal output → does not feed goal-diff tiebreaks).\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/models/__init__.py` — export `OrderedLogitModel`, `OutcomeProbabilities`, `fit_ordered_logit` (additive; keep legacy baseline exports).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_ordered_logit.py` — fit on a synthetic frame where large `elo_diff` correlates with home wins; assert rows sum to 1 and within [0,1], monotonic `prob_home` vs `elo_diff`, determinism on re-fit, trains on `dataset.train` only, and that `from statsmodels.miscmodels.ordinal_model import OrderedModel` imports.\n- Conventions: frozen dataclass value objects, DI of config, deterministic fit, mypy strict, ruff line-length 100.\nEOF\n)"', 'description': 'Create ordered logit issue'}
