```

**Design rationale**: #12 is a dependency-light foundation (`models/dataset.py` chronological no-shuffle split + `y_outcome`/`y_margin` targets, plus `HybridConfig`/`OrderedLogitConfig` wired into `AppConfig` + `default.toml`). #13 (primary, goal-based RF/GBM) and #14 (secondary ordered logit) are independent of each other and parallelizable. #15 is the no-key end-to-end capstone that verifies both models fit through the real Elo→Poisson→features path and that the retained legacy baseline still constructs.

**Agent assignment**: every task is pure-Python sklearn/statsmodels/pandas modeling, so all map to `python-pro` + the `python-expert` skill (`solid-principles` always active) — no frontend/backend-web specialist applies. Out-of-scope Cycle-5 work (Monte-Carlo simulation, RPS/Brier backtests, odds scraping, new CLI commands) is explicitly excluded in every issue body.
